{
  "stem": "13457.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 1.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And he left and then came to my aunt in Rudna.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "The reason why I'm mentioning it, because subsequently, he called for us from Rudna to come out of Warsaw and join him in Rudna.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "In the meantime, just as a side remark, the, the Polish soldiers that were then herded together by the Russians were subsequently, the officers, were, were killed in Katyn Forest.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "So it, it was first sort of a miracle that--not that miracle, but his enterprising spirit that he left that group.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, back to us in Warsaw, the messenger came from Pa-- from my father saying, join me in Rudna.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By that time, the Jews couldn't travel already on the trains.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the idea was how to get the tickets?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my fa-- my mother found a Polish woman.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She-- my mother-- gave her enough money to buy tickets for us by train to, to, to the border between, then, Germany and Russia.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so the woman bought the tickets for herself, for us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And also, my mother was enterprising enough that she gave her more money.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one wounded Polish soldier was there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is to make, to make the group bigger, so we, as Jews, won't be as conspicuous as standing out in, in the group.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was well, well-thought-out, too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We-- I remember the day we packed up and were going to do the railroad station to-- of course, in cattle trains to go to the border.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I remember I was standing with my mother next to the-- how do you call these-- heating stoves, big, tile stoves.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And at that time, I was nine years old.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I told my mother that I have a feeling that-- as we are leaving the apartment-- that we'll never come back.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
